{
  "stem": "7739.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's tragic what happened to everybody, but it touches me when I think of him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father was involved, although he was a businessman-- he was friends with the people in town who had mostly to do with the courts.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm not sure until today, whether he had a license to practice law or he studied law and he didn't finish school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So the judges and the lawyers and the official in the court were his friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] whether he was clever enough, or he had the knowledge, I don't know, that he predicted exactly what it is going to happen to the Jews, and he made arrangements for everybody in the family to be situated in such a state where we will be saved from expulsion, from being sent away to other places.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Like he knew that other places are being-- that the Jewish people are being rounded up and taken away to farms in the Ukraine, or whatever else.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The Germans were saying that they were taking the Jews away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he arranged for me and my brother-- to the front of his-- Jozef Kowacki, he was a famous lawyer in town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had a big [NON-ENGLISH] or farm near [NON-ENGLISH] called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was supposed to hide us out there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What year was this, do you know?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in 1942.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He also made arrangements for all the family to obtain work permits.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had ammunition factories in town, although Jews were not permitted to work there before the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "During the war after the occupation, the Germans allowed Jews to be employed there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father got a job in these factories and so did my older brother.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
